RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Lynnwood, WA operates under a mayor-council government with a full-time mayor and seven city council members elected at-large for four-year staggered terms. Mayor Christine Frizzell took office in January 2022. The listed council members are based on the official City of Lynnwood website. Recent election results from November 2025 indicate that Derica Escamilla and Robert Leutwyler retained their council seats, while Bryce Owings and Isabel Mata were elected. This suggests potential changes to the council's composition for upcoming terms, with Bryce Owings likely replacing Josh Binda. However, as of the current date, the official city website lists the provided council members. The phrase 'The next Lynnwood City Council is beginning to take shape' in the election results article suggests these results are for the upcoming council, typically taking office in January of the following year.
